%20a%20Jeju%20Air%20Boeing%20737-800%20series%20aircraft%20crashed%20and%20burst%20into%20flames%20is%20seen%20at%20Muan%20International%20Airport%20on%20Monday.%3Cp%3EJUNG%20YEON-JE%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Jeju%20Air%20plane%20crashed%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20killing%20179%20of%20181%20on%20board.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestigators%20are%20considering%20the%20role%20of%20a%20bird%20strike%20in%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBird%20strikes%20have%20not%20caused%20many%20plane%20losses%2C%20and%20experts%20say%20it%20may%20not%20be%20the%20only%20factor.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBird%20strike%20is%20being%20considered%20as%20a%20possible%20cause%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeju-air-boeing-plane-crash-south-korea-airport-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20plane%20crash%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20killed%20almost%20everyone%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20colliding%20with%20birds%20has%20always%20been%20a%20risk%20of%20flying%2C%20it%20has%20brought%20down%20comparatively%20few%20modern%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20said%20of%20the%20Sunday%20crash%20that%20a%20bird%20strike%20was%20unlikely%20to%20be%20the%20sole%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20bird%20strike%20should%20be%20a%20survivable%20event%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sonya%20Brown%2C%20an%20aerospace-design%20lecturer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20New%20South%20Wales%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Fdec%2F30%2Fbird-strike-unlikely-sole-cause-of-fatal-south-korean-plane-crash-experts-say%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20with%20The%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20planes%20are%20designed%20to%20cope%20with%20bird%20strikes.%20Engine-builders%20have%20long%20tested%20their%20designs%20by%20launching%20bird%20carcasses%20into%20running%20engines%20to%20ensure%20they%20keep%20working%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20this%20CNBC%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2017%2F11%2F24%2Fgive-thanks-for-the-fowl-shot-into-jet-engines-in-the-name-of-safety.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20article%20from%202017.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20June%20report%20by%20the%20US%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20said%20wildlife%20strikes%20on%20civilian%20and%20military%20aircraft%20have%20killed%20491%20people%20and%20destroyed%20some%20350%20aircraft%20globally%20between%201988%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20in%20the%20US%2C%2049%20civil%20aircraft%20were%20lost%20because%20of%20birds%20in%20the%20period%20between%201990%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivil%20aircraft%20include%20both%20airliners%20and%20general%20aviation%20planes.%20The%20latter%20are%20more%20susceptible%20to%20damage%20because%20many%20are%20smaller%2C%20have%20less%20robust%20airframes%2C%20and%20single%20engines.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20may%20sound%20a%20lot%2C%20it%20represents%20a%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20total%20losses%20over%20that%20period%20of%20more%20than%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20more%20than%2027%2C000%20aircraft%20fatalities%20between%201988%20and%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Aviation%20Safety%20Network%2C%20putting%20bird%20strikes%20as%20a%20factor%20in%20fewer%20than%201.8%25%20of%20deaths.%20Most%20of%20the%20deaths%20involve%20general%20aviation%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBird%20strikes%20on%20passenger%20jetliners%20very%20rarely%20bring%20down%20an%20aircraft.%20The%20last%20time%20it%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20was%20the%202009%20crash-landing%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-was-passenger-sully-miracle-on-the-hudson-jal-crash-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BMiracle%20on%20the%20Hudson%26quot%3B%2C%20where%20everyone%20survived.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20bird%20strikes%20will%20cause%20damage%20to%20airlines%2C%20but%20pilots%20are%20safely%20able%20to%20land%20the%20plane.%20American%20Airlines%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fpossible-bird-strike-american-airlines-jet-emergency-landing-jfk-airport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuffered%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20bird%20strike%20over%20New%20York%20in%20December%20and%20circled%20back%20to%20the%20airport%20for%20an%20emergency%20landing%2C%20with%20no%20reported%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22392680bf-e555-4379-938b-158deed58f55%5C%22%3EThe%20Jeju%20crash%20reason%20is%20still%20unknown%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20have%20yet%20to%20give%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20loss%20of%20the%20Jeju%20Air%20flight%2C%20a%20Boeing%20737-800.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20in%20South%20Korea's%20transport%20ministry%20official%20said%20the%20airport's%20control%20tower%20issued%20a%20bird%20strike%20warning%20before%20the%20crash%2C%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fplane-drives-off-runway-crashes-airport-south-korea-yonhap-reports-2024-12-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fire%20chief%20at%20Muan%20International%20Airport%2C%20where%20the%20plane%20crashed%2C%20said%20in%20a%20televised%20briefing%20that%20an%20investigation%20will%20consider%20whether%20birds%20stuck%20the%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korea's%20acting%20president%20ordered%20an%20emergency%20inspection%20of%20the%20country's%20airline%20operations.%20And%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2F2024%2F12%2F30%2Fsouth-korea-orders-emergency-airline-safety-inspection-after-fatal-crash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20will%20audit%20all%20101%20of%20the%20country's%20737-800s%20with%20US%20investigators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20bird%20strike%20is%20being%20considered%20as%20a%20cause%2C%20or%20a%20possible%20factor.%20And%20other%20issues%20have%20been%20reported%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVideo%20footage%20showed%20that%20the%20plane%20landed%20without%20its%20landing%20gear%20deployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeith%20Tonkin%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Aviation%20Projects%2C%20an%20aviation%20consulting%20company%20in%20Australia%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20appears%20that%20the%20aircraft%20wasn't%20configured%20for%20a%20normal%20landing%20%E2%80%94%20the%20landing%20gear%20wasn't%20down%2C%20and%20it%20looks%20like%20the%20wing%20flaps%20weren't%20extended%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommentators%20have%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20design%20of%20the%20airport%20%E2%80%94%20the%20plane%20came%20to%20a%20hard%20stop%20when%20it%20hit%20a%20solid%20wall%20near%20the%20runway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Guzzetti%2C%20a%20former%20accident%20investigator%20at%20the%20US's%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20and%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Flive%2F2024%2F12%2F28%2Fworld%2Fsouth-korea-plane-crash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplane-crash-survival-data-seating-crew-azerbaijan-airlines-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplane%20crashes%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20typically%20the%20result%20of%20multiple%20factors%20at%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-airlines-crash-swiss-cheese-holes-may-explain-collision-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSwiss%20Cheese%20Model%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20aviation%2C%20a%20theory%20that%20says%20a%20string%20of%20multiple%20smaller%20errors%20often%20lead%20to%20an%20air%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20aviation%20industry%20is%20built%20on%20redundancy%2C%20and%20there%20are%20very%20few%20single-point%20failures%20in%20airplane%20design%20or%20airplane%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BTypically%2C%20it's%20a%20combination%20of%20factors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-korea-plane-crash-bird-strike-not-caused-many-fatal-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735559134000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677277699de00e389eb3bf72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-korea-plane-crash-bird-strike-not-caused-many-fatal-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bird%20strike%20is%20a%20possible%20cause%20of%20the%20fatal%20Jeju%20Air%20crash%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20but%20many%20experts%20say%20they%20are%20skeptical%20it's%20the%20only%20factor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A107%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-korea-plane-crash-bird-strike-not-caused-many-fatal-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Laapata%20Bollywood%3A%20How%202024%20Became%20The%20Year%20Of%20Banality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fpu0aqui_m_625x300_25_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%3E%3Csmall%3E%3Cem%3E(A%20scene%20from%20Baby%20John)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsmall%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20good%20year%20in%20the%20movies%20can%20mean%20multiple%20things.%20Studios%20sufficiently%20bankrolling%20films%2C%20independent%20projects%20finding%20their%20way%20to%20the%20mainstream%2C%20underdogs%20triumphing%20over%20tentpole%20projects%2C%20new%20faces%20coming%20up%20and%20old%20faces%20rediscovering%20their%20voice.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%202024%20fulfilled%20most%20of%20these%20possibilities.%20Filmmaker%20Sriram%20Raghavan%2C%20known%20for%20curating%20gore%20in%20his%20films%2C%20conjured%20a%20heartbreaking%20romance%20in%20%3Cem%3EMerry%20Christmas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Three%20female%20actors%20fronted%20the%20commercially%20viable%20%3Cem%3ECrew%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20modest-budgeted%20%3Cem%3EMunjya%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewon%20big%2C%20Payal%20Kapadia's%20independently-funded%20%3Cem%3EAll%20We%20Imagine%20As%20Light%3C%2Fem%3E%20got%20a%20theatrical%20release%20and%20ensembles%20like%20%3Cem%3EMadgaon%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EStree%202%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EBhool%20Bhulaiyaa%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20triumphs.%20On%20paper%2C%20we%20are%20steadying%20ahead.%20But%20a%20little%20probing%20dismantles%20this%20neat%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20can%2C%20and%20should%2C%20be%20different%20ways%20of%20looking%20at%20something.%20But%20no%20matter%20how%20one%20sees%20it%2C%202024%20reveals%20to%20be%20uninspiring%20for%20Hindi%20films.%20Quantity%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20problem.%20Admittedly%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lull%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20crisis%2C%20but%20some%20time%20has%20passed%20and%20as%20of%20now%2C%20a%20steady%20roster%20of%20theatrical%20and%20streaming%20releases%20is%20in%20place.%20Theatre%20owners%20and%20exhibitors%20also%20came%20up%20with%20a%20ploy%20to%20combat%20infrequent%20releases%3A%20re-releasing%20old%20Hindi%20films.%20Yet%2C%20the%20quality%20has%20been%20on%20a%20steady%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Era%20Of%20'Genericness'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20the%20landscape%20of%20Hindi%20films%20resembles%20a%20linear%20line%20drawn%20by%20a%20vanishing%20ink.%20The%20multi-crore%20industry%20has%20come%20to%20be%20imbued%20by%20such%20genericness%20in%20plot%20and%20aesthetics%20that%20is%20hard%20to%20locate%20its%20identity.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20long%20the%20line%20is%E2%80%94and%20how%20expansive%20the%20industry%20is%20becoming%E2%80%94the%20growth%20feels%20incidental%2C%20for%20the%20ambition%20is%20stunted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20have%20been%20the%20post-pandemic%20uncertainty%2C%20the%20easy%20availability%20of%20other%20Indian%20language%20films%20through%20streaming%20sites%20during%20that%20period%2C%20or%20the%20gigantic%20successes%20of%20those%20ventures.%20In%202022%2C%20S.S.%20Rajamouli's%20%3Cem%3ERRR%20%3C%2Fem%3Eregistered%20the%20highest%20opening%20by%20an%20Indian%20film%3B%20this%20year%2C%20another%20Telugu%20language%20film%2C%20Sukumar's%20%3Cem%3EPushpa%202%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20became%20the%20highest-grossing%20Indian%20film%20in%20the%20first%20week.%20But%20evidently%2C%20the%20monopoly%20of%20Hindi%20films%20and%20its%20false%20equivalence%20with%20Indian%20cinema%20have%20considerably%20weakened.%20The%20diversity%20of%20the%20industry%20has%20been%20steamrolled%20into%20a%20prickly%20homogeneity%20where%20any%20two%20films%20look%20the%20same%2C%20the%20scale%20feels%20identical%2C%20the%20action%20looks%20uniformly%20designed%20and%20the%20style%20is%20fashioned%20in%20self-reflexive%20humour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20is%20often%20the%20case%2C%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20paved%20the%20way.%20His%202023%20film%20%3Cem%3EPathaan%20%3C%2Fem%3Enot%20just%20marked%20his%20return%20to%20the%20screen%20after%20a%20four-year%20hiatus%20but%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20outings%20that%20earned%20money%20at%20a%20time%20many%20others%20struggled%20to%20do%20so.%20Its%20success%20did%20three%20things%3A%20it%20reiterated%20the%20supremacy%20of%20Khan%2C%20legitimised%20action%20as%20a%20thriving%20genre%2C%20and%20recognised%20star%20cameos%20in%20films%20as%20the%20onset%20of%20multiverses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpectacle%20Over%20Everything%20Else%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20most%20Hindi%20films%20can%20be%20slotted%20in%20these%20distinct%20categories.%20Rohit%20Shetty's%20%3Cem%3ESingham%20Again%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20his%20version%20of%20a%20(cop)%20multiverse%2C%20and%20the%20production%20house%20Maddock%20Films%20furthered%20its%20horror-comedy%20universe%20with%3Cem%3E%20Stree%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EMunjya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Sagar%20Ambre%20and%20Pushkar%20Ojha%20helmed%20the%20action-thriller%20%3Cem%3EYodha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Siddharth%20Anand%20directed%20the%20aviation%20(action)%20thriller%3Cem%3E%20Fighter%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Ali%20Abbas%20Zafar%20made%20the%20abysmal%20%3Cem%3EBade%20Miyan%20Chote%20Miyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EBMCM%3C%2Fem%3E).%20There%20are%20more%20examples%3A%20Nikkhil%20Advani%20leaned%20on%20action%20with%20%3Cem%3EVedaa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Ravi%20Udyawar%20did%20the%20same%20with%20%3Cem%3EYudhra%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20so%20did%20Aditya%20Datt%20in%20%3Cem%3ECrakk%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Clubbing%20them%20together%20could%20be%20reductive%2C%20but%20it%20is%20difficult%20not%20to%20identify%20the%20sweeping%20attempt%20by%20the%20makers%20to%20treat%20plot%20as%20an%20accessory%20to%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%2C%20meta%20references%20clog%20the%20screenplay.%20Khan's%20famous%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBete%20ko%20hath%20lagane%20se%20pehle%2C%20baap%20se%20baat%20kar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(%26quot%3BBefore%20touching%20the%20son%2C%20deal%20with%20the%20father%26quot%3B)%2C%20rooted%20to%20the%20personal%20turmoil%20of%20his%20son's%20arrest%20in%202021%2C%20spawned%20similar%20iterations%20post%20%3Cem%3EJawan%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2023).%20Tiger%20Shroff%20repeated%20his%20meme-famous%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Echoti%20bachi%20ho%20kya%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(%26quot%3Bare%20you%20a%20little%20girl%26quot%3B)%20a%20decade%20later%20in%20%3Cem%3EBMCM%20%3C%2Fem%3Eafter%20mouthing%20them%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20%3Cem%3EHeropanti%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2014)%3B%20Chitrangada%20Singh%20briefly%20appeared%20in%20Akshay%20Kumar's%20%3Cem%3EKhel%20Khel%20Mein%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2024)%20and%20their%20scenes%20were%20scored%20to%20the%20music%20of%20%3Cem%3EDesi%20Boyz%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20the%20last%20film%20they%20did%20together.%20The%20subtext%20here%20is%20actors%20winking%20directly%20at%20the%20audience%20and%20establishing%20a%20connection%20despite%20the%20fourth%20wall.%20But%20Hindi%20films%20have%20never%20seemed%20more%20distant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStuck%20On%20Repeat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%202024%20proved%20anything%2C%20it%20is%20that%20what%20works%20really%20does%2C%20and%20when%20it%20does%2C%20it%20is%20repeated.%20The%20success%20of%20%3Cem%3EStree%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EBhool%20Bhulaiyaa%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20furthered%20the%20accomplishment%20of%20sequels%2C%20and%20now%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20in%20the%20works.%20The%20Ranbir%20Kapoor-starrer%20%3Cem%3EAnimal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2023)%20ended%20with%20the%20announcement%20of%20%3Cem%3EAnimal%20Park%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20supposed%20to%20go%20on%20floors%20in%202027.%20Varun%20Dhawan%20is%20part%20of%20%3Cem%3ENo%20Entry%202%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EBorder%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20reportedly%20a%20sequel%20to%20%3Cem%3EJugjugg%20Jeeyo%3C%2Fem%3E%20too.%20Vikas%20Bahl's%20%3Cem%3EShaitaan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20minted%20money%20this%20year%2C%20has%20a%20sequel%20in%20the%20making%2C%20and%20in%20October%2C%20actor%20Salman%20Khan%20and%20producer%20Sajid%20Nadiadwala%20confirmed%20working%20on%20%3Cem%3EKick%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20a%20cheeky%20Instagram%20post.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20is%20rumoured%20to%20be%20featuring%20in%20%3Cem%3EPathaan%202%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20actor%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20is%20either%20working%20in%20a%20sequel%20or%20wants%20to%20be%20in%20one.%20It%20is%20a%20jarring%20trend%20that%20spells%20a%20creative%20crisis%20in%20Hindi%20cinema%20with%20a%20damning%20pronouncement.%20As%20of%20this%20moment%2C%20filmmakers%20are%20more%20involved%20in%20catering%20to%20the%20audience%20than%20creating%20for%20them.%20Budgets%20are%20being%20amped%20up%2C%20more%20investment%20is%20tailored%20for%20VFX%20and%20Hindi%20films%20are%20getting%20bigger.%20Yet%2C%20one%20would%20be%20hard-pressed%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20trailers%20of%2C%20say%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBaby%20John%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EAnimal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20is%20the%20same%20story%20everywhere%3A%20overgrown%20men%20fighting%20with%20an%20obscure%20vengeance%20to%20prove%20their%20manhood%20rather%20than%20seek%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBankruptcy%20Of%20Imagination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20this%20crystallises%20the%20most%20terrifying%20symptom%20of%20Hindi%20cinema%20today%20where%20the%20bankruptcy%20of%20imagination%20has%20manifested%20in%20accentuating%20machismo.%20More%20and%20more%20films%20centre%20around%20men%20who%20need%20an%20excuse%20to%20draw%20out%20blood%20from%20the%20next%20person.%20The%20face%20does%20not%20matter%2C%20nor%20does%20the%20cause.%20While%20they%20thumped%20about%20the%20screens%2C%20smaller%20and%20more%20inventive%20projects%2C%20such%20as%20Sanjay%20Tripaathy's%20warm%20%3Cem%3EBinny%20And%20Family%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Karan%20Gour's%20whimsical%20%3Cem%3EFairy%20Folk%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Shoojit%20Sircar's%20affecting%20%3Cem%3EI%20Want%20to%20Talk%3C%2Fem%3E%20battled%20for%20more%20screens%20and%20our%20attention.%20Even%20Kiran%20Rao's%20wonderful%20%3Cem%3ELaapataa%20Ladies%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Varun%20Grover's%20perceptive%20%3Cem%3EAll%20India%20Rank%3C%2Fem%3E%20garnered%20appreciation%20once%20they%20landed%20on%20digital%20platforms.%20Once%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20they%20would%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20as%20multiplex%20films.%20Today%2C%20they%20are%20too%20ambitious%20for%20streaming%20and%20too%20atypical%20for%20theatres.%20They%20reside%20in%20a%20no%20man's%20land%2C%20and%20in%20their%20dislocation%2C%20they%20mirror%20the%20gradual%20distortion%20of%20Hin