5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediverse%20needs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20found%20that%20parenting%20with%20an%20emphasis%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautonomy-supported-parenting-choice-within-limits-improves-wellbeing-study-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20essential%20for%20all%20of%20our%20well-being.%20Here's%20how%20we%20landed%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b99a979-7e67-4832-a6c1-689ebc28e805%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20typical%20advice%20didn't%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20received%20his%20diagnosis%20first%2C%20at%20age%203.%20I%20stuck%20to%20the%20conventional%20wisdom%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcatered-my-son-every-whim-he-has-little-self-esteem-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparenting%20autistic%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20strict%20routines%2C%20visual%20cues%2C%20and%20an%20emphasis%20on%20predictability%20and%20structure.%20But%20these%20strategies%20repeatedly%20backfired%20in%20our%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimply%20asking%20my%20son%20to%20get%20dressed%20in%20the%20morning%20often%20started%20the%20day%20with%20battles%20that%20drained%20us%20both.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20thought%20he%20was%20being%20defiant%2C%20but%20I%20learned%20it%20wasn't%20about%20the%20pants%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20demand%20itself.%20His%20provider%20suggested%20he%20might%20identify%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveling-with-neurodivergent-child-can-be-hard-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPathological%20Demand%20Avoidance%3C%2Fa%3E%20(PDA)%2C%20a%20cluster%20of%20traits%20individuals%20often%20experience%20extreme%20anxiety%20about%20everyday%20demands.%20For%20children%20like%20mine%2C%20even%20a%20small%20request%20can%20feel%20unbearable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20then%20discovered%20low%20demand%20parenting%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20lowering%20stress%20and%20anxiety.%20I