e%20immediate.%20His%20anxiety%20decreased%2C%20and%20he%20became%20more%20curious%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-responsibility-chores-made-them-confident-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econfident%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20clarify%2C%20a%20high%20autonomy%20approach%20doesn't%20mean%20chaos.%20It%20means%20creating%20a%20framework%20where%20my%20kids%20made%20choices%20within%20safe%20boundaries.%20For%20example%2C%20bedtime%20didn't%20dissolve%20into%20%26quot%3BWhatever%2C%20stay%20up%20all%20night.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20wonder%20how%20much%20sleep%20you%20need%20to%20feel%20good%20tomorrow.%20Let's%20figure%20it%20out%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20my%20son%20typically%20tells%20us%20he's%20ready%20for%20bed%20around%208%20pm%20and%20asks%20for%20help%20if%20needed.%20Real-world%20feedback%20worked%20better%20than%20any%20lecture%20or%20power%20struggle%2C%20and%20he%20owns%20his%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%2C%20who%20is%20younger%2C%20also%20chooses%20her%20clothes%2C%20meals%2C%20and%20bedtime%20routine.%20As%20these%20decisions%20became%20theirs%20to%20make%2C%20anxiety%20decreased%2C%20and%20emotional%20regulation%20improved.%20And%20as%20my%20kids%20felt%20more%20in%20control%2C%20so%20did%20I.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250818694-e23c-442b-8b99-831a7b105d92%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20this%20means%20for%20us%20today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%2C%20now%207%2C%20is%20thriving.%20He%20used%20to%20struggle%20with%20anxiety%2C%20but%20now%20enjoys%20giving%20presentations%20at%20our%20homeschool%20co-op.%20My%20daughter%2C%20now%203%2C%20is%20growing%20into%20a%20confident%2C%20self-aware%20child%20who%20already%20knows%20her%20voice%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20every%20day%20is%20perfect.%20Sometimes%20I%20miss%20the%20%26quot%3Bold%20rules%26quot%3B%20when%20things%20feel%20messy%