3BGrowing%20up%20there%20was%20a%20nightmare%2C%20especially%20after%202011.%20All%20the%20time%20scared%2C%20armed%20personnel%20everywhere%2C%20and%20corruption%20rampant.%20It%20was%20like%20living%20in%20a%20big%20prison.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsyria-war-bashar-al-assad-damascus-how-syrian-teens-graffiti-became-bashar-al-assads-writing-on-the-wall-7199318%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHow%20A%20Syrian%20Teen%20Triggered%20Al-Assad's%20Fall%20With%20Graffiti%2013%20Years%20Ago%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbu%20Khaled%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20computer%20science%20engineer%20from%20Jableh%2C%20reflected%20the%20collective%20disbelief.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20in%20shock.%20We%20did%20not%20expect%20that%20the%20day%20would%20come%20when%20this%20regime%20would%20fall%20because%20of%20its%20brutal%20oppressive%20methods.%20My%20reaction%20and%20that%20of%20the%20Syrian%20people%20when%20we%20learned%20of%20Assad's%20escape%20and%20that%20the%20revolution%20had%20succeeded%20was%20that%20we%20took%20to%20the%20streets%20and%20chanted%20at%20the%20top%20of%20our%20voices%2C%20'Long%20live%20free%20Syria.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20subjected%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20repression.%20The%20regime%20treated%20us%20like%20slaves.%20Speaking%20out%2C%20even%20in%20general%20terms%2C%20could%20result%20in%20detention%20or%20worse.%20Secret%20detention%20centres%2C%20forced%20disappearances%2C%20and%20torture%20camps%20were%20part%20of%20our%20reality.%20If%20you%20posted%20a%20video%20on%20social%20media%20criticising%20the%20government%2C%20security%20forces%20would%20storm%20your%20house%20and%20drag%20you%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Abu%20Khaled%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAftermath%20Of%20Regime%20Change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%20Assad's%20ouster%2C%20scenes%20of%20jubilation